1
00:00:48,330 --> 00:00:50,570
It isn't the location,

2
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:55,010
and it isn't fatigue.

3
00:00:55,010 --> 00:00:57,040
I think I fell asleep...

4
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:59,250
because someone stayed with me.

5
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:01,580
I want to see you.

6
00:01:03,150 --> 00:01:05,590
No one will use that blanket,

7
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:07,920
so come whenever you want to sleep well.

8
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:13,030
Since I can't go to the semi-basement.

9
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:18,830
I can hear the thoughts in your head.

10
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:21,470
It is what you're thinking.

11
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,670
You're right.

12
00:01:30,010 --> 00:01:33,350
(A Piece of Your Mind)

13
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:57,400
(Episode 9)

14
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,340
You haven't given up, have you?

15
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:00,970
Are you going to say silly things again?

16
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:03,540
Don't. I'm totally at peace right now.

17
00:02:03,980 --> 00:02:06,210
Good, and you know why.

18
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,210
It's all because of these guys.

19
00:02:08,820 --> 00:02:10,550
There's definitely a reason.

20
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:14,120
One day, out of the blue, you wake up...

21
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:17,320
and there are 100 reasons why you shouldn't like him.

22
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,760
- How did you... - Keep listening.

23
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:23,430
Kang In Wook and Han Seo Woo focus only on work...

24
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,570
even if they're alone in a dark place.

25
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:27,670
It's incomprehensible to others.

26
00:02:28,530 --> 00:02:31,300
Whether nothing happens or something does happen,

27
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:32,610
there's definitely a reason.

28
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:34,470
Think about it.

29
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:37,110
You'll have one silly, simple,

30
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:40,350
and useless reason come to mind.

31
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,080
You'll be here, right?

32
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:48,020
Mr. Kang doesn't need me for his rehearsal.

33
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:49,390
Please stay with him.

34
00:02:57,530 --> 00:02:59,400
There has to be a reason.

35
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,870
I must put Ji Soo back in her place.

36
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:11,710
Mr. Kang.

37
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:15,150
I like your piece.

38
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:18,620
It's so good, that I hear it in my head before I fall asleep.

39
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:21,520
How did you write a piece like that?

40
00:03:21,650 --> 00:03:23,420
If even someone like me likes it,

41
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:25,490
it means it's really good. Right?

42
00:03:25,690 --> 00:03:27,290
Did you listen to it enough to have it stuck in your head?

43
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:29,630
It got stuck right away.

44
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:33,100
Do you mind if I listen here?

45
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,540
Suit yourself.

46
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:55,460
- Will you step aside a bit? - Pardon?

47
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:57,860
Okay.

48
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,660
You don't have to go that far.

49
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:04,660
Okay.

50
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:35,990
Oh my gosh.

51
00:05:37,690 --> 00:05:40,260
I'm here because Soon Ho asked me to fix the blinds.

52
00:05:41,330 --> 00:05:43,360
Did she send you too?

53
00:05:43,460 --> 00:05:44,930
No, that's...

54
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:47,900
You could just say yes.

55
00:05:51,340 --> 00:05:52,340
Tell me.

56
00:05:53,170 --> 00:05:55,440
You don't have time to see me,

57
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,410
so why do you come to see my apartment?

58
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:02,520
What's the difference between seeing me and seeing my place?

59
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:07,190
Did you do it on purpose?

60
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:11,020
Stop and turn back, and look only briefly.

61
00:06:13,530 --> 00:06:14,560
Yes.

62
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,630
You can't lie.

63
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,770
- That's... - We miss each other.

64
00:06:20,930 --> 00:06:22,240
We want to be with each other.

65
00:06:26,410 --> 00:06:27,610
We want to hold hands.

66
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,640
It's my first time having it be mutual.

67
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:40,920
That's just my case.

68
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,690
Are you going to stay? I'll leave.

69
00:06:45,690 --> 00:06:46,690
No.

70
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,130
Soon Ho, are you still there?

71
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,670
How are the plants you took from my place?

72
00:07:34,670 --> 00:07:36,440
They're well. You know me.

73
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:47,020
I thought they were the only things my wife left behind.

74
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:51,320
She left an unexpected way out...

75
00:07:53,130 --> 00:07:54,990
for me to escape.

76
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:57,760
Playing this song,

77
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,270
I feel like I can breathe.

78
00:08:03,970 --> 00:08:05,070
My wife...

79
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:11,010
is gone from this world.

80
00:08:34,430 --> 00:08:36,800
I got the results from my physical.

81
00:08:38,770 --> 00:08:41,540
What does it say? Nothing's wrong, right?

82
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:45,210
The doctor said...

83
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:49,320
he had never seen such a clean and transparent colon before.

84
00:08:54,050 --> 00:08:55,320
When I heard that,

85
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,760
I wondered why I was so stressed.

86
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:00,190
I felt all my stresses melt away.

87
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:03,430
It really bugged me to see him...

88
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:05,560
every morning and evening after breaking up.

89
00:09:06,530 --> 00:09:08,300
Most people don't see each other after breaking up,

90
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,870
but we do.

91
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:11,600
It has its perks.

92
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,040
People usually break up not to see each other.

93
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:17,080
Office romances. They keep seeing each other after breaking up too.

94
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,610
They don't cook breakfast for the other.

95
00:09:18,610 --> 00:09:20,210
- Should I kick him out? - Yes.

96
00:09:20,210 --> 00:09:22,110
Aren't you his friend?

97
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:23,380
It's hard on you.

98
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:25,080
Breakups are hard for everyone.

99
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,020
- Not Chang Sup. - Darn you.

100
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,720
Anyway, I'm good for now.

101
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,590
What about you?

102
00:09:33,090 --> 00:09:35,700
Tell me 1 more among the 100 reasons.

103
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:39,400
Why all of a sudden?

104
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,670
You'd better have 100.

105
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:42,270
I'm going to hear all 100.

106
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:44,340
Well, he...

107
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:46,240
What was that?

108
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:49,280
Tell me the 100 reasons. Tell me.

109
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:52,140
You don't have 100, do you? Why are you lying, you brat?

110
00:09:52,140 --> 00:09:53,450
Tell me the 100 reasons.

111
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,820
Tell me the 100 reasons.

112
00:09:58,420 --> 00:10:00,750
The 100 reasons.

113
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,790
He kept telling me.

114
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:08,730
I need you, Seo Woo.

115
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:10,900
Stay with me.

116
00:10:11,330 --> 00:10:14,170
To come. To stay with him.

117
00:10:14,170 --> 00:10:16,270
- We miss each other. - That he misses me.

118
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:19,040
We want to be with each other. We want to hold hands.

119
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,010
It's my first time having it be mutual.

120
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,740
There's no reason why I shouldn't go.

121
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:30,150
This is clearly mutual.

122
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,270
- It's that thing. - That thing.

123
00:11:22,470 --> 00:11:23,500
Take it.

124
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,230
It suddenly got cold.

125
00:11:48,830 --> 00:11:50,100
That must be uncomfortable.

126
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,760
You'll strain your back and shoulders.

127
00:11:52,330 --> 00:11:54,230
There's a way.

128
00:11:55,770 --> 00:12:00,510
Doing this improves circulation in my legs and helps me fall asleep.

129
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:02,360
How did you know?

130
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:05,060
I could feel you staring at me.

131
00:14:08,770 --> 00:14:10,370
Did it snow?

132
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:21,380
It's spring snow.

133
00:14:21,950 --> 00:14:24,350
Everything sounds pretty with the word "spring" in it.

134
00:14:24,820 --> 00:14:27,790
Spring snow, spring night, spring ache.

135
00:14:29,490 --> 00:14:30,590
Spring ache?

136
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:31,920
Yes.

137
00:14:32,420 --> 00:14:36,460
When you get so lonely in the spring that your body aches.

138
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:41,000
It's not exactly a word, but Eun Joo and I made it up.

139
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,600
I woke up at the sound of snow.

140
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:48,810
You heard the snow fall?

141
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,280
You can't hear it in Seoul.

142
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:56,580
You barely hear it in the dead quiet countryside...

143
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:59,420
when snow piles up on crocks outside.

144
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:04,220
I hear it from time to time ever since I was 18.

145
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:45,130
That's fascinating.

146
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:50,640
It's my first recording today.

147
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:53,370
I'm doing the official recording.

148
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:00,280
It snowed in secret. It's a good sigh.

149
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,710
Keep sweeping.

150
00:16:31,310 --> 00:16:32,580
Now.

151
00:16:35,650 --> 00:16:36,680
That side too.

152
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:54,730
Oh, gosh.

153
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:58,970
Are you okay?

154
00:16:58,970 --> 00:17:00,310
It's nothing.

155
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:03,740
I'm afraid I'm making you even more nervous.

156
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,740
Didn't you hurt your hand?

157
00:17:06,410 --> 00:17:08,580
I rarely get hurt.

158
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,420
You're the one I'm worried about.

159
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,720
Do you think I can do a good job?

160
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:14,820
Of course.

161
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:18,020
How's the pianist's condition?

162
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,830
I tried my best to maximize it,

163
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:22,590
but he chose the piece yesterday.

164
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,860
It'll go well.

165
00:17:24,860 --> 00:17:28,100
With Kang In Wook's skills, it'll be a piece of cake.

166
00:17:29,330 --> 00:17:30,870
Give me some of your Midas touch.

167
00:17:46,290 --> 00:17:47,420
Shall we begin?

168
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,090
Okay.

169
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:20,980
That one sounded good.

170
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:25,780
Let's go with that.

171
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,990
Okay.

172
00:19:34,930 --> 00:19:36,430
You were great.

173
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:37,730
You too.

174
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:42,030
Thank you for making sure this song doesn't disappear.

175
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:48,470
I'll send you the file and discuss with you before I upload it.

176
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,710
If you want to play it for someone, do it beforehand.

177
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:53,550
There's no such person.

178
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:57,820
I'm really tired right now.

179
00:19:57,820 --> 00:19:59,080
Oh, okay.

180
00:20:19,910 --> 00:20:21,110
Well...

181
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:33,150
It's a happy day. What's with the long faces?

182
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,460
- Good work. - Good job.

183
00:20:45,230 --> 00:20:47,700
- All right. - Here.

184
00:20:48,030 --> 00:20:49,030
Thank you.

185
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:50,740
- Gosh. - It's delicious.

186
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:52,040
You're right.

187
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:53,370
- Is it good? - Yes.

188
00:20:53,770 --> 00:20:57,180
He's good at making other delivery food,

189
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:59,140
but not fried chicken.

190
00:20:59,910 --> 00:21:02,050
I'm always so sad at nights when I crave chicken and beer.

191
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:03,480
Our chef isn't that good...

192
00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:06,590
at making fried chicken and Pyongyang cold noodles.

193
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:11,360
Our lab will be perfect if those two issues are resolved.

194
00:21:11,660 --> 00:21:14,390
Didn't he say he could make cold noodles?

195
00:21:14,390 --> 00:21:16,060
He just wings it.

196
00:21:17,030 --> 00:21:19,970
The noodles become stiff if you use too much pressure.

197
00:21:19,970 --> 00:21:22,530
But if you use too little, they get brittle.

198
00:21:22,530 --> 00:21:26,040
The pressure has to be perfect to get the right chewiness.

199
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,640
But it's so difficult.

200
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,780
I should donate a noodle-making machine or something.

201
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:31,410
- I'm against it. - Thanks.

202
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:34,180
I've even thought of where to place it. Hey, wipe your mouth.

203
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:37,150
But it takes up too much space.

204
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:40,790
The pressure should be pumped... Hey.

205
00:21:41,950 --> 00:21:43,760
There's a design in your shed.

206
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:45,460
It's still there.

207
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,360
You haven't gotten rid of it?

208
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:49,390
Hold up, hold up.

209
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:52,930
Okay, that's good.

210
00:21:54,470 --> 00:21:56,670
Hey. I'm off starting today.

211
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,000
Cheers.

212
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,240
- Sure. - Cheers.

213
00:22:01,740 --> 00:22:03,510
- Take some time to relax. - I will.

214
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,190
The plant you wanted...

215
00:22:19,490 --> 00:22:21,290
is Seo Woo's, so I can't give you that one.

216
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:22,590
But here.

217
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:28,870
What is this?

218
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:30,300
I bought it a few days ago.

219
00:22:31,270 --> 00:22:34,470
I wanted to use it today, but I don't think I should.

220
00:22:35,970 --> 00:22:37,340
A few days ago...

221
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:41,410
Before you told me about your wife.

222
00:22:43,850 --> 00:22:45,080
Today is a happy day.

223
00:22:45,450 --> 00:22:47,420
You're allowed to use them today.

224
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:51,460
But that's just my opinion. It's up to you.

225
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,990
Jin Soo, breakfast!

226
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,530
Why is a chair missing?

227
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,930
Ms. Kim took it.

228
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:36,330
I see.

229
00:23:38,870 --> 00:23:39,870
No.

230
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,740
What's with him?

231
00:23:47,610 --> 00:23:49,650
This is the emergency key when I was in that room.

232
00:23:49,650 --> 00:23:50,650
Why?

233
00:23:50,980 --> 00:23:53,890
Well... You know. A rope from the ceiling.

234
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:55,150
It's a common method.

235
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:58,390
Like in crime dramas. An inn, ceiling, chair...

236
00:23:59,190 --> 00:24:01,060
- Shouldn't you open the door? - What are you talking about?

237
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:04,130
This isn't an inn. Don't be ridiculous.

238
00:24:05,730 --> 00:24:07,730
- Oh, no. What do I do? - I'll open it.

239
00:24:07,730 --> 00:24:09,500
- The key. Hurry. - Oh, no.

240
00:24:09,670 --> 00:24:10,840
Oh, no.

241
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,110
No!

242
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:26,050
Oh my gosh.

243
00:24:27,420 --> 00:24:28,920
What did you write there?

244
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:32,120
How could I remember? It was so many years ago.

245
00:24:32,620 --> 00:24:35,230
You're the girl who used to live in this room?

246
00:24:35,230 --> 00:24:36,360
The college kid Min Jung?

247
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:38,000
Who are you calling a kid?

248
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:41,630
You were just in middle school. You rude punk.

249
00:24:42,130 --> 00:24:44,970
You aged so much. You look completely different.

250
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,740
I thought you were older than I was when I first saw you.

251
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:53,380
She said I was a rich girl because I was inheriting this homestay.

252
00:24:53,380 --> 00:24:55,850
You have no idea how frustrated I was.

253
00:24:55,850 --> 00:24:57,280
- I was right. - How so?

254
00:24:58,050 --> 00:25:00,550
You won't do anything rash, right?

255
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:03,490
- Why would I? - What is this?

256
00:25:03,490 --> 00:25:05,460
You wrote a boy's name and erased it.

257
00:25:06,090 --> 00:25:07,390
Seo Joon Hee?

258
00:25:08,890 --> 00:25:12,060
Yes, I remember. I was so silly back then.

259
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,600
There's another one. Cha... Cha Hyun Woo?

260
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,270
It was scratched out.

261
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,700
I should erase it if we broke up.

262
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:19,970
How many is that?

263
00:25:19,970 --> 00:25:22,140
You should've erased it properly. This wasn't your ceiling.

264
00:25:22,140 --> 00:25:23,240
I was popular.

265
00:25:25,210 --> 00:25:27,350
"I'm so happy. It's exciting."

266
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:29,180
"Let's not forget today."

267
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:30,980
"May 2002."

268
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,750
- What day was that? - I don't know. I don't remember.

269
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,860
You said not to forget.

270
00:25:37,060 --> 00:25:38,890
Whatever it was, it must have been exciting.

271
00:25:40,930 --> 00:25:43,330
So that's where she was. The cheerful Min Jung.

272
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,070
Are you good?

273
00:25:47,630 --> 00:25:50,640
