It's something that happened when I was young.

554
00:49:50,100 --> 00:49:51,340
How young?

555
00:49:54,710 --> 00:49:56,110
When I lived in Norway.

556
00:49:56,810 --> 00:49:58,850
How bad could it be?

557
00:49:59,250 --> 00:50:00,880
As long as no one died.

558
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:02,050
What if someone did die?

559
00:50:04,420 --> 00:50:05,520
Look how shocked you are.

560
00:50:07,190 --> 00:50:08,590
I wasn't shocked.

561
00:50:11,090 --> 00:50:13,660
When we moved around in Europe,

562
00:50:14,890 --> 00:50:17,530
I avoided Koreans so that I could adapt.

563
00:50:19,130 --> 00:50:20,700
I was young and just didn't like it.

564
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:25,240
I never spoke Korean.

565
00:50:27,010 --> 00:50:29,640
There was a Korean boy that I hated.

566
00:50:30,480 --> 00:50:31,880
Why did you hate him?

567
00:50:33,510 --> 00:50:34,510
No.

568
00:50:35,150 --> 00:50:37,750
That doesn't matter. Sure, you could hate him.

569
00:50:38,390 --> 00:50:39,390
So?

570
00:50:40,650 --> 00:50:42,160
Sure, I could hate him.

571
00:50:43,460 --> 00:50:44,860
That doesn't matter.

572
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:50,200
Correct.

573
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:05,650
It was snowing.

574
00:51:06,080 --> 00:51:07,250
Hard.

575
00:51:08,920 --> 00:51:11,050
- Gosh, I'm sorry. - It's okay.

576
00:51:13,250 --> 00:51:15,260
Are you Korean?

577
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:18,390
You've been walking past here since two months ago, right?

578
00:51:18,430 --> 00:51:21,560
You didn't answer, so I didn't think you were Korean.

579
00:51:22,330 --> 00:51:24,330
Do you go to Eva Lawson High School?

580
00:51:25,430 --> 00:51:27,900
Everyone was taking shelter in the school,

581
00:51:28,970 --> 00:51:31,000
but before I knew it, I said...

582
00:51:35,210 --> 00:51:37,340
Ha Won is coming this way right now.

583
00:51:45,250 --> 00:51:46,390
So,

584
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:49,590
are you saying someone was in an accident because of a lie...

585
00:51:49,590 --> 00:51:51,520
you told when you were a kid?

586
00:51:54,530 --> 00:51:55,860
Why is that...

587
00:51:59,330 --> 00:52:01,030
You shouldn't have told me.

588
00:52:01,430 --> 00:52:04,440
This is nothing if you say it's nothing.

589
00:52:04,440 --> 00:52:06,110
You shouldn't have told me.

590
00:52:06,240 --> 00:52:08,040
It was just an accident.

591
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:10,740
Why can't you...

592
00:52:13,180 --> 00:52:14,950
If you'd just say it's okay...

593
00:52:14,950 --> 00:52:16,420
How is that okay?

594
00:52:16,420 --> 00:52:17,480
Ji Soo.

595
00:52:21,820 --> 00:52:24,290
You can't do this. Back then, I...

596
00:52:26,690 --> 00:52:27,930
Won...

597
00:52:28,900 --> 00:52:30,800
How could you do that to Won?

598
00:52:32,830 --> 00:52:35,740
Ji Soo. Why can't you take my side?

599
00:52:35,900 --> 00:52:37,500
Why?

600
00:52:39,140 --> 00:52:41,110
If you say it's okay,

601
00:52:41,110 --> 00:52:43,140
I'll be able to breathe.

602
00:52:45,010 --> 00:52:47,150
Why couldn't she take my side?

603
00:52:50,680 --> 00:52:53,020
If only she had taken my side.

604
00:52:57,460 --> 00:52:59,330
It's no big deal.

605
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:01,690
It's okay.

606
00:53:06,370 --> 00:53:07,730
It's okay.

607
00:53:28,520 --> 00:53:31,090
Play what you recorded with the piano tuner.

608
00:53:31,090 --> 00:53:32,660
I'll know when I hear it.

609
00:53:33,060 --> 00:53:36,330
There's a feeling of finality in a final piece. I'll find it.

610
00:53:39,830 --> 00:53:41,430
Are you ready?

611
00:53:41,700 --> 00:53:43,100
I can't wait.

612
00:53:43,540 --> 00:53:45,670
The pianist is Kang In Wook.

613
00:54:10,630 --> 00:54:12,070
I'm scared,

614
00:54:12,900 --> 00:54:14,230
but it's beautiful.

615
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:18,640
You shouldn't have told me.

616
00:54:19,970 --> 00:54:22,710
I found out why Won's mom died.

617
00:54:23,210 --> 00:54:26,650
It wasn't the blizzard.

618
00:54:27,810 --> 00:54:30,950
Why can't you take my side? Why? Why?

619
00:54:30,950 --> 00:54:33,050
My husband was involved.

620
00:54:34,890 --> 00:54:37,160
It's too much to bear on my own.

621
00:54:37,820 --> 00:54:39,830
I want to tell the world,

622
00:54:40,690 --> 00:54:42,630
but I can't.

623
00:54:44,130 --> 00:54:46,100
That's why I'm writing you like this.

624
00:54:47,630 --> 00:54:51,100
With the assurance that it will never be read.

625
00:55:21,030 --> 00:55:22,840
Go with Ms. Moon.

626
00:55:23,700 --> 00:55:26,070
She's more reliable than my mom.

627
00:55:26,340 --> 00:55:27,770
I'll be relieved then.

628
00:55:29,640 --> 00:55:31,010
It won't snow.

629
00:55:31,980 --> 00:55:33,250
I can't leave.

630
00:55:35,210 --> 00:55:36,350
Leave.

631
00:55:37,520 --> 00:55:40,550
I'll stay behind and find out the reason.

632
00:55:57,640 --> 00:55:58,870
Look at the ceiling.

633
00:56:01,640 --> 00:56:03,080
It's soothing.

634
00:56:17,620 --> 00:56:18,860
Got it.

635
00:56:22,200 --> 00:56:26,000
I found out why I sold...

636
00:56:26,830 --> 00:56:28,130
my dishes.

637
00:56:30,200 --> 00:56:33,310
I found out the reason.

638
00:56:35,210 --> 00:56:36,440
I found out...

639
00:56:38,180 --> 00:56:39,450
the reason.

640
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:49,140
Not the blizzard. Maybe someone was involved.

641
00:56:49,140 --> 00:56:50,710
An external factor.

642
00:56:51,580 --> 00:56:54,210
She wasn't even in a shelter and died in a random place.

643
00:56:54,210 --> 00:56:56,920
We questioned and argued it more than 1,000 times.

644
00:56:56,950 --> 00:56:58,420
It looked like she went to pick you up...

645
00:56:58,420 --> 00:57:00,390
That's what I couldn't understand.

646
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:03,460
She knew the rules for evacuation better than anyone.

647
00:57:04,020 --> 00:57:05,960
Either the midway shelter or at the school.

648
00:57:07,390 --> 00:57:10,660
She knew that better than anyone. Why would she go there?

649
00:57:10,660 --> 00:57:11,700
Won.

650
00:57:12,930 --> 00:57:15,070
I think Ji Soo found out something recently.

651
00:57:15,600 --> 00:57:18,810
Ji Soo? If it were something you had to know,

652
00:57:18,810 --> 00:57:20,740
wouldn't she have told you?

653
00:57:21,310 --> 00:57:24,180
I'm sure she didn't because it wasn't worth telling you.

654
00:57:25,780 --> 00:57:27,380
She wanted to see you.

655
00:57:28,210 --> 00:57:30,380
She wrote you countless letters.

656
00:57:30,380 --> 00:57:33,750
If she tried to tell me and not you, that means you didn't need to know.

657
00:57:34,550 --> 00:57:36,920
I'm positive there was another reason.

658
00:57:36,920 --> 00:57:38,990
I'll sound like an old fogy, but I'll say it anyway.

659
00:57:38,990 --> 00:57:41,090
There are many things that make you miserable once you find out,

660
00:57:41,090 --> 00:57:42,700
and many things that you're better off not knowing.

661
00:57:42,700 --> 00:57:45,060
I'm not scared at all...

662
00:57:45,060 --> 00:57:48,100
about what will happen afterward, or what will get better.

663
00:57:51,170 --> 00:57:52,940
What I fear most is...

664
00:57:55,170 --> 00:57:57,340
living without knowing something that I should know.

665
00:58:00,510 --> 00:58:02,010
It's so cold.

666
00:58:02,480 --> 00:58:04,120
It's nippy at night.

667
00:58:07,920 --> 00:58:08,960
Won.

668
00:58:11,290 --> 00:58:12,890
When I first met you...

669
00:58:13,490 --> 00:58:14,760
in Boston...

670
00:58:16,060 --> 00:58:20,000
Remember how it would snow up to our knees?

671
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:23,500
Right? But someone was standing in the middle of the street,

672
00:58:23,500 --> 00:58:26,310
looking up at the sky like this.

673
00:58:26,310 --> 00:58:30,080
With his neck bent all the way like it was about to snap.

674
00:58:30,640 --> 00:58:32,250
But I looked closer,

675
00:58:33,210 --> 00:58:37,020
and he was glaring at the sky.

676
00:58:37,480 --> 00:58:38,720
Talk about intense.

677
00:58:40,990 --> 00:58:42,020
Won.

678
00:58:43,760 --> 00:58:45,020
Kim Ji Soo...

679
00:58:46,690 --> 00:58:48,690
probably thought about it whenever it snowed too...

680
00:58:48,690 --> 00:58:50,400
and realized recently...

681
00:58:50,400 --> 00:58:54,600
that what happened to Won's mom wasn't purely because of the snow,

682
00:58:54,600 --> 00:58:56,370
but another reason...

683
00:58:57,170 --> 00:59:00,810
Very peacefully... She must have realized...

684
00:59:01,810 --> 00:59:03,140
something...

685
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:07,580
I feel like perhaps she wanted to tell you that.

686
00:59:07,580 --> 00:59:09,080
I do have an idea.

687
00:59:09,080 --> 00:59:10,150
What?

688
00:59:10,280 --> 00:59:11,750
The cause of Ji Soo's misery.

689
00:59:11,750 --> 00:59:14,920
You worked so hard for years not to know about her husband.

690
00:59:15,290 --> 00:59:17,290
I never said it was her husband.

691
00:59:17,960 --> 00:59:20,990
Well, isn't that what you mean? You said you wouldn't find out.

692
00:59:21,690 --> 00:59:23,060
Keep it that way.

693
00:59:35,540 --> 00:59:36,610
What's up?

694
00:59:36,610 --> 00:59:37,610
Hey, Soon Ho.

695
00:59:37,980 --> 00:59:38,980
Yes?

696
00:59:38,980 --> 00:59:41,080
Is Kim Ji Soo's husband not Korean?

697
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:43,380
Why do you care? That's what I want to know.

698
00:59:43,380 --> 00:59:46,750
I thought Ji Soo and Ha Won were the only Koreans in Norway.

699
00:59:46,750 --> 00:59:48,350
That's why they're so tight.

700
00:59:48,690 --> 00:59:50,290
It was just the two of them.

701
00:59:50,920 --> 00:59:53,590
Anyway, don't you dare ask Uncle things like that.

702
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:55,600
He left his cell phone.

703
00:59:55,700 --> 00:59:57,460
He needs his phone.

704
00:59:57,460 --> 00:59:59,630
- He left it intentionally. - Why?

705
00:59:59,900 --> 01:00:01,600
He's shutting out the world.

706
01:00:03,370 --> 01:00:04,740
Whatever. Let him be.

707
01:00:05,040 --> 01:00:07,240
- Aren't you coming here? - Why would I?

708
01:00:07,240 --> 01:00:08,740
I'm mad busy. Bye.

709
01:00:10,740 --> 01:00:11,840
Why is she getting mad?

710
01:00:22,660 --> 01:00:23,860
Hey, you.

711
01:00:25,060 --> 01:00:27,030
Why are you loitering in front of my house? Move.

712
01:00:30,500 --> 01:00:32,130
Why are you smiling?

713
01:00:32,470 --> 01:00:33,800
I'm here to see Seo Woo.

714
01:00:35,940 --> 01:00:37,000
Oh, 100 reasons...

715
01:00:39,540 --> 01:00:40,870
Hello.

716
01:00:48,710 --> 01:00:50,280
Come in.

717
01:00:57,260 --> 01:00:59,490
She isn't picking up.

718
01:00:59,730 --> 01:01:01,290
Didn't you call first?

719
01:01:02,860 --> 01:01:04,260
I'll go to the studio.

720
01:01:04,660 --> 01:01:06,000
Please tell her to come there.

721
01:01:06,900 --> 01:01:08,300
I forgot my phone.

722
01:01:09,540 --> 01:01:11,140
Have you had breakfast?

723
01:01:11,500 --> 01:01:13,740
It's okay. My stomach isn't well.

724
01:01:13,740 --> 01:01:14,810
No.

725
01:01:15,110 --> 01:01:16,910
If I let you go without giving you at least water,

726
01:01:16,910 --> 01:01:18,380
Seo Woo will have my head.

727
01:01:21,850 --> 01:01:22,880
Come on.

728
01:01:29,390 --> 01:01:30,860
When your stomach is bothering you,

729
01:01:30,860 --> 01:01:32,390
nothing beats scorched rice.

730
01:01:50,210 --> 01:01:51,210
It's nice.

731
01:01:53,050 --> 01:01:55,780
Why did you come without making plans first?

732
01:01:58,750 --> 01:02:00,150
I must have come because I wanted to see her.

733
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:02,520
You're not here to tell her something bad, are you?

734
01:02:03,090 --> 01:02:04,790
I don't like Seo Woo being sad.

735
01:02:04,960 --> 01:02:06,030
No.

736
01:02:06,760 --> 01:02:08,160
When I see her,

737
01:02:10,100 --> 01:02:11,400
I can stop thinking.

738
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:13,800
I feel at ease.

739
01:02:14,430 --> 01:02:16,470
Seo Woo has that effect, doesn't she?

740
01:02:18,270 --> 01:02:20,240
When I look at her, I feel encouraged.

741
01:02:21,470 --> 01:02:22,610
I'm like that too.

742
01:02:25,750 --> 01:02:27,050
But...

743
01:02:27,750 --> 01:02:30,850
why does Seo Woo have so many reasons?

744
01:02:32,890 --> 01:02:36,660
She said she liked someone, but 100 reasons stood in her way.

745
01:02:37,490 --> 01:02:39,090
I asked her to tell me each one,

746
01:02:39,090 --> 01:02:40,690
and they were all stupid.

747
01:02:43,400 --> 01:02:44,730
Tell me just one.

748
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:49,070
She felt like someone else's misery was her happiness.

749
01:02:49,070 --> 01:02:50,240
How stupid.

750
01:02:50,640 --> 01:02:51,700
Right?

751
01:02:53,340 --> 01:02:55,310
She's a tough cookie,

752
01:02:55,310 --> 01:02:56,940
but she gets depressed when it counts.

753
01:02:56,940 --> 01:02:58,510
You know how she's splat on her face at times.

754
01:02:58,510 --> 01:03:00,080
She's all dejected.

755
01:03:00,310 --> 01:03:02,150
"I don't know. I won't do it."

756
01:03:02,150 --> 01:03:03,380
"Leave me alone."

757
01:03:03,620 --> 01:03:05,580
Imagining 100 reasons...

758
01:03:05,790 --> 01:03:07,790
and she withdraws herself.

759
01:03:09,420 --> 01:03:10,520
Does it taste bad?

760
01:03:10,790 --> 01:03:12,490
Why aren't you eating? You're hurting my feelings.

761
01:03:16,730 --> 01:03:17,800
It's good.

762
01:03:41,350 --> 01:03:42,460
Oh my gosh.

763
01:03:54,300 --> 01:03:55,500
Something's up, isn't it?

764
01:03:56,470 --> 01:03:57,600
What is it this time?

765
01:03:58,840 --> 01:04:00,370
Tell me.

766
01:04:02,880 --> 01:04:04,410
You're acting strange.

767
01:04:06,510 --> 01:04:07,550
What...

768
01:04:11,920 --> 01:04:14,490
Go home. Don't wander around.

769
01:04:17,790 --> 01:04:19,190
You're going home, right?

770
01:04:22,930 --> 01:04:24,760
- I came to see Seo Woo. - Seo Woo?

771
01:04:25,330 --> 01:04:27,870
She's out recording Mr. Kang.

772
01:04:28,470 --> 01:04:30,070
We're filming a music video. Cool, right?

773
01:04:30,540 --> 01:04:32,270
We want to do as much PR as we can.

774
01:04:32,870 --> 01:04:35,140
- Did you make an appointment? - No.

775
01:04:36,280 --> 01:04:37,380
I just missed her.

776
01:04:38,080 --> 01:04:39,580
Oh my gosh. Hey.

777
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:44,280
- Is that... Is that... - That's right.

778
01:05:05,300 --> 01:05:06,570
I can't do this here.

779
01:05:13,350 --> 01:05:14,450
It echoes too much.

780
01:05:19,290 --> 01:05:22,250
Just... Just pretend to play.

781
01:05:22,660 --> 01:05:24,760
We're doing this live because you insisted.

782
01:05:25,260 --> 01:05:27,930
We'll edit the video to the music anyway,

783
01:05:27,930 --> 01:05:29,060
so let's just do it.

784
01:05:29,660 --> 01:05:30,960
It's not like it's classical music.

785
01:05:46,750 --> 01:05:49,480
Ms. Moon considered the poster for the recital...

786
01:05:49,480 --> 01:05:51,280
and wanted a location that would look nice.

787
01:05:51,280 --> 01:05:53,090
That's why she chose this place.

788
01:05:53,490 --> 01:05:55,090
So you haven't been here.

789
01:05:55,790 --> 01:05:58,590
Even if that's why Soon Ho chose it, you should've checked it out.

790
01:06:01,660 --> 01:06:03,830
Narrowing it down to locations we can use right away,

791
01:06:03,830 --> 01:06:05,400
first is our studio,

792
01:06:05,400 --> 01:06:07,470
second is Mr. Choi's studio.

793
01:06:08,030 --> 01:06:09,540
We can check his schedule.

794
01:06:09,540 --> 01:06:12,100
Or maybe somewhere you used to live?

795
01:06:12,100 --> 01:06:14,470
Someone you're familiar with may be good too.

796
01:06:14,870 --> 01:06:15,910
Home would be nice.

797
01:06:16,340 --> 01:06:18,410
The apartment where I lived when I was four.

798
01:06:18,780 --> 01:06:20,780
My aunt's house is in Oslo.

799
01:06:21,680 --> 01:06:22,820
Does that work?

800
01:06:23,780 --> 01:06:25,520
How will we find a house with good acoustics in time?

801
01:06:26,950 --> 01:06:28,450
I do know of one.

802
01:06:29,190 --> 01:06:31,220
My friend said it has good acoustics.

803
01:06:33,760 --> 01:06:34,790
Never mind.

804
01:06:36,860 --> 01:06:39,230
Second. Mr. Choi's studio.

805
01:06:39,770 --> 01:06:40,770
Okay.

806
01:06:56,080 --> 01:06:58,520
- You startled me. - Were you startled?

807
01:06:59,520 --> 01:07:00,750
By this?

808
01:07:01,050 --> 01:07:03,260
I was so startled earlier that I almost fainted.

809
01:07:03,790 --> 01:07:05,990
- Did you hear? - What happened?

810
01:07:07,690 --> 01:07:11,000
As you can see. The acoustics were bad enough,

811
01:07:11,200 --> 01:07:14,600
but the director said, "It isn't classical music."

812
01:07:14,800 --> 01:07:17,000
So we're filming in Mr. Choi's studio.

813
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:19,870
- I already arranged it. - No. It's not pretty there.

814
01:07:19,870 --> 01:07:22,370
It's pretty here, but the acoustics are horrible.

815
01:07:25,410 --> 01:07:26,480
You punk.

816
01:07:28,450 --> 01:07:29,850
That's right.

817
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:32,420
That's why you were so arrogant toward me.

818
01:07:33,150 --> 01:07:34,520
Seo Woo, you little...

819
01:07:37,960 --> 01:07:39,460
(Hoon)

820
01:07:43,430 --> 01:07:45,000
I said I won't come.

821
01:07:51,340 --> 01:07:52,600
(Eun Joo)

822
01:07:52,600 --> 01:07:54,940
Did you see the guy who wanted to see you?

823
01:07:58,710 --> 01:08:00,150
(Phone)

824
01:08:00,680 --> 01:08:04,350
(Before Dawn)

825
01:08:07,720 --> 01:08:09,560
The phone is turned off.

826
01:08:15,030 --> 01:08:16,700
This is a big mess.

827
01:08:16,700 --> 01:08:20,600
All the plants at the entrance are dead.

828
01:08:21,970 --> 01:08:23,070
There's no way.

829
01:08:23,540 --> 01:08:25,370
- Send me a picture. - Come right away.

830
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:26,910
Look for yourself.

831
01:08:29,140 --> 01:08:32,380
What... This punk. What's his problem?

832
01:08:32,980 --> 01:08:34,380
I'm going now.

833
01:08:36,420 --> 01:08:37,450
Let's go.

834
01:09:17,990 --> 01:09:19,220
They're fine.

835
01:09:28,800 --> 01:09:29,970
He lied to me.

836
01:09:30,700 --> 01:09:31,770
Where is he?

837
01:09:46,790 --> 01:09:48,150
How pretty.

838
01:09:50,860 --> 01:09:52,020
Hoon, where are you?

839
01:09:55,030 --> 01:09:56,800
- They're totally fine. - Hold up.

840
01:09:56,800 --> 01:09:58,960
Soon Ho. Hold up.

841
01:09:59,360 --> 01:10:00,970
You need to save me.

842
01:10:01,900 --> 01:10:02,970
(My husband was involved)

843
01:10:02,970 --> 01:10:04,000
What's this?

844
01:10:04,170 --> 01:10:06,370
Ji Soo's husband killed Won's mom?

845
01:10:06,870 --> 01:10:09,510
Oh my gosh. That psycho.

846
01:10:09,940 --> 01:10:11,610
How could this be?

847
01:10:12,540 --> 01:10:14,150
Where can I find this jerk?

848
01:10:14,150 --> 01:10:15,650
I need to question him.

849
01:10:15,650 --> 01:10:16,820
I'm against it.

850
01:10:17,350 --> 01:10:18,420
Are you kidding me?

851
01:10:18,420 --> 01:10:21,720
You can't do anything with this. It'll only torment Won.

852
01:10:22,020 --> 01:10:25,220
Hoon. Let's say for argument's sake that Won catches that jerk.

853
01:10:25,220 --> 01:10:29,060
Once he finds out what happened, he'll end it right there.

854
01:10:29,660 --> 01:10:32,030
He's still Ji Soo's husband. He wouldn't do anything harsh.

855
01:10:32,030 --> 01:10:33,930
He won't do anything harsh? He should.

856
01:10:33,930 --> 01:10:37,870
Regardless, I don't care who he is. We have to catch him and finish him.

857
01:10:38,470 --> 01:10:39,640
I'll take care of it.

858
01:10:39,710 --> 01:10:42,670
Okay. Then rip it up. I trust you.

859
01:10:42,670 --> 01:10:43,780
You rip it up.

860
01:10:43,780 --> 01:10:45,440
It's your letter.

861
01:10:47,150 --> 01:10:50,980
Seriously. Ji Soo has such a tough life.

862
01:10:53,490 --> 01:10:55,550
(From Kim Ji Soo, To Moon Jung Sook)

863
01:10:57,060 --> 01:10:59,260
I found out...

864
01:10:59,790 --> 01:11:01,060
why I sold...

865
01:11:02,460 --> 01:11:03,730
my dishes.

866
01:11:04,430 --> 01:11:06,900
No. Never. She can never find out.

867
01:11:07,870 --> 01:11:09,970
She can't find out what happens to her.

868
01:11:09,970 --> 01:11:11,970
The more we talk, the more she finds out.

869
01:11:11,970 --> 01:11:14,540
And if we're unlucky, she'll find out everything.

870
01:11:14,540 --> 01:11:16,980
In the place that you like...

871
01:11:16,980 --> 01:11:19,440
with the ambience that you like.

872
01:11:19,440 --> 01:11:22,110
Since you like it right before the sun sets.

873
01:11:22,680 --> 01:11:24,020
We're right on time.

874
01:11:25,120 --> 01:11:27,220
The pianist is Kang In Wook.

875
01:11:27,950 --> 01:11:31,690
What touched you, Ji Soo?

876
01:11:44,170 --> 01:11:45,240
Won,

877
01:11:46,170 --> 01:11:47,970
do you want to go to Norway?

878
01:11:49,370 --> 01:11:51,710
You just have to say one thing.

879
01:11:51,740 --> 01:11:53,210
If Won says it's okay.

880
01:11:53,210 --> 01:11:56,580
Ji Soo said her husband made a mistake.

881
01:11:56,580 --> 01:11:57,850
The cause of Ji Soo's misery.

882
01:11:57,850 --> 01:12:01,020
You worked so hard for years not to know about her husband.

883
01:12:01,020 --> 01:12:02,920
I never said it was her husband.

884
01:12:03,060 --> 01:12:05,520
I found out why Won's mom died.

885
01:12:48,200 --> 01:12:50,500
(A Piece of Your Mind)

886
01:12:51,040 --> 01:12:52,370
Do you know about him?

887
01:12:52,370 --> 01:12:53,770
I like him a lot.

888
01:12:53,770 --> 01:12:56,580
Kim Ji Soo. That's my friend's name.

889
01:12:56,880 --> 01:12:58,510
Should I just ruin it?

890
01:12:58,540 --> 01:13:00,650
Don't hold it in. Scream and let it out.

891
01:13:02,350 --> 01:13:03,720
I'll stay with you.

892
01:13:04,420 --> 01:13:05,820
Do you want to live here?

893
01:13:06,150 --> 01:13:08,390
I like this place because there's nothing here.

894
01:13:08,390 --> 01:13:10,320
I guess you can't afford a frying pan.

895
01:13:10,320 --> 01:13:12,020
I can fill it.

896
01:13:12,020 --> 01:13:13,860
Why are things getting so complicated?

897
01:13:13,860 --> 01:13:15,630
He's dying to know.

898
01:13:15,860 --> 01:13:19,060
Ha Won and Kang In Wook can never meet.

